description: In Being and Nothingness, Jean-Paul Sartre argued that human existence is not defined by what we are, but by what we project ourselves toward. We are not fixed beings—we are always becoming, shaping our identities through imagined futures, chosen selves, and ideal versions of who we might be. In this sense, every Ghibli-style portrait is more than stylised nostalgia; it’s existential projection—a quiet act of longing. AI does not merely render an image; it renders a desire—like what we might see in the Mirror of Erised from the Harry Potter universe, which shows our deepest wants.

The bill, which has not yet been introduced in the Lok Sabha, has sparked opposition due to concerns it would hinder the Waqf Board’s powers.
title: 'Will badly affect Muslims': TN CM Stalin moves motion against Waqf bill

description: A woman from Meerut threatened her alcoholic husband with dismemberment if he didn't change his behavior. The husband, who had visible injuries from being hit with a brick, reached the police but decided to reconcile without filing a formal complaint. The couple has been struggling with frequent disputes due to the husband's drinking habit.
title: 'Will chop you, seal you in drum': UP woman threatens alcoholic husband

description: Unidentified individuals hurled bombs and opened fire outside BJP leader Arjun Singh's residence in Bhatpara, causing injuries to a youth. Singh accused TMC councillor Sunita Singh's son of the attack, while TMC's Jagaddal MLA accused Singh's group of instigating violence. Police and RAF personnel were deployed to restore order, finding empty cartridges and live bombs on-site.
title: Bombs hurled, shots fired outside BJP leader's house in West Bengal

description: Security forces have cordoned off an area in J&K's Kathua district after terrorists were spotted. Reports indicate an exchange of fire occurred as forces initiated a search operation in the Ghati Juthana area. This search is part of an ongoing anti-terror effort that began four days ago.
title: Encounter breaks out in J&K's Kathua, security forces launch search operation

description: Infosys has laid off 30-45 trainees at its Mysuru campus after they failed evaluation tests, continuing from a similar cut in February. Affected trainees have been offered alternative career paths and assistance with accommodations and transportation as needed. Infosys also modified its hybrid work policy, requiring employees to work from the office at least 10 days a month.
title: Infosys to trainees amid Mysuru layoffs: You have not met the..."

description: Indian wrestler Nitesh earned a bronze medal in the Greco-Roman category at the Senior Asian Wrestling Championship 2025 in Amman, Jordan. His impressive 9-0 victory over Amanberdi Agamammedov of Turkmenistan added to the bronze earlier secured by Sunil Kumar in the men's 87kg division, highlighting India's strong performance in the championship.
title: Nitesh wins bronze in Greco Roman at Asian Wrestling C'ships

description: Five CISF personnel, pretending to be income tax officers, were arrested along with three accomplices for a heist in Bengal. The gang, orchestrated by a CISF inspector in collusion with the victim's stepmother, raided a home, seizing cash and jewelry. All accused have been suspended and are under investigation.
title: 'Special 26' turns real: 5 CISF officers arrested in WB for posing as I-T officers

description: Steve Jobs previously expressed concerns about U.S. tech reliance on foreign-made components, warning that outsourcing could hollow out the industry. Similarly, President Trump has implemented measures like tariffs on auto imports and reconsidering the CHIPS Act to boost domestic manufacturing and reduce dependency on global supply chains.
title: Steve Jobs may have agreed with Donald Trump's 'biggest policy' 36 years ago

description: Canada’s Liberal Party revoked Indian-origin MP Chandra Arya’s bid for the party leadership and his nomination in his own constituency due to alleged ties with the Indian government, including undisclosed meetings with Indian officials. Arya denies these allegations and cites his opposition to the Khalistan movement as a possible reason.
title: Canada's Liberal Party bars MP from running under party’s banner for India ties

description: World Cricketers' Association raises questions over functioning of cricket but evades direct "on-record" questions on the findings of the report
title: Cricket players' body report questions ICC revenue distribution

description: Sunil Gavaskar highlights Rahul Dravid's decision to share prize money equally among his support staff after the T20 World Cup, questioning if current coach Gautam Gambhir will do the same following the Champions Trophy win. Gavaskar praised BCCI's generous financial rewards for players and staff, demonstrating appreciation for their efforts.
title: Gavaskar questions if Gambhir will emulate Dravid

description: Salman Khan has reacted to death threats while he's promoting his upcoming movie 'Sikandar' which is set to release on Eid, March 30. It sees him alongside Rashmika Mandanna.
title: 'Jitni umar likhi hai ... ': Salman on death threats from Lawrence Bishnoi

description: Tamil Nadu CM MK Stalin criticizes UP CM Yogi Adityanath for his comments on the three-language policy and delimitation, accusing the BJP of being rattled by Tamil Nadu's stance. Stalin emphasizes opposition to the imposition of Hindi and calls for dignity and justice.
title: 'Political black comedy at its darkest': Stalin slams Yogi's 'hate' remark

description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened flat in trade on Thursday. While BSE Sensex was near 77,300, Nifty50 was below 23,500.
title: Stock market today: BSE Sensex opens flat; Nifty50 below 23,500
'CBI raids done to generate content for PM Modi’s speech,' says Bhupesh Baghel

description: Top stock market recommendations: Aakash K Hindocha, Deputy Vice President at Nuvama Professional Clients Group, recommends buying Affle, Amara Raja Energy & Mobility, and Bharti Airtel stocks. He provides insights into Nifty and Bank Nifty indices, highlighting potential movement and targets amidst recent rallies and price actions.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock recommendations for March 27, 2025

description: US President Donald Trump announced a 25% tariff on all imported vehicles and key auto parts, impacting Tesla and other automakers. Although Tesla assembles its cars in the US, it relies on foreign parts, increasing production costs. Analysts predict price hikes and reduced vehicle production across North America, exacerbating Tesla's market challenges amid rising competition.
title: Trump announces 25% tariffs on imported cars: How it may help Musk and Tesla

description: US president Donald Trump signed an executive order imposing a 25% tariff on foreign-manufactured vehicles, effective from April 2. The move has triggered threats of retaliation from trading partners, with significant impacts already seen in Asian automotive markets. Japan and Canada are evaluating counter-measures, while additional trade levies are expected next week.
title: Trump signs 25% auto tariff order; markets slump, allies consider countermeasures
Buy or sell: Stock recommendations for today

description: The Pittsburgh Steelers were primarily focused on pursuing Aaron Rodgers as their quarterback. Consequently, Russell Wilson decided to sign with the New York Giants. Wilson, now their starting QB, aims to lead the Giants effectively. Meanwhile, the Steelers remain patient, awaiting Rodgers' decision, which could significantly impact the team's future.
title: 'I expect to be the starter': Russell Wilson breaks silence on Giants’ offseason wait

description: The personal and sensitive information of senior advisers in Trump's administration, including mobile numbers, email addresses, and passwords, have been leaked online. This data, connected to various digital platforms, could be used for phishing attacks and cyber threats, highlighting significant security risks.
title: Personal information of Trump's security officials found online: Report

description: India and China are striving to mend ties post the 2020 Galwan valley clashes, with some issues still outstanding. External affairs minister S Jaishankar emphasized the significance of managing differences constructively, noting that peace at the border is crucial for the overall relationship between the two nations.
title: ‘Tense relationship serves neither side’: Jaishankar on rebuilding India-China ties

description: John Abraham's film 'The Diplomat' enters its second week with steady collections, reaching a total of ₹28.10 crore despite a drop on its second Monday. Meanwhile, Vicky Kaushal's 'Chhaava' outperforms 'Diplomat' in its sixth week, amassing a total of ₹586.35 crore.
title: 'The Diplomat' box office collection day 13

description: A Turkish doctoral student, Rumeysa Ozturk, was detained by federal immigration agents due to her pro-Palestinian activism. With a valid student visa, Ozturk's arrest and subsequent transfer to Louisiana have drawn scrutiny and legal challenges, citing potential violations of her rights and court orders.
title: Watch: Masked ICE agents detain Turkish student over pro-Palestine activism

description: The DRI has arrested Ballari-based jeweller Sahil Sakariya Jain for his involvement in an extensive gold smuggling racket with Sandalwood actor Ranya Rao. Sahil aided Ranya in smuggling 14.5 kg of gold, resulting in a significant financial loss to the exchequer. Investigations revealed frequent communications and assistance in disposing of the smuggled gold.
title: Gold smuggling case: DRI arrests K'taka businessman who 'helped' Ranya Rao

description: Deliberations are underway in Kolkata to redefine the term 'bir muktijoddha' to only include battlefield fighters and classify others as 'Liberation War Associates'. This proposal has sparked debates and raised concerns about the recognition and possible ignoring of genuine freedom fighters and the distorting of historical contributions.
title: Bangladesh plan to redefine ‘muktijoddha’ yet again stirs a debate in West Bengal

description: The Indian government criticized the US Commission on International Religious Freedom (USCIRF) for its annual report, which raised concerns about India's treatment of minorities and recommended sanctions against RAW. The foreign ministry accused USCIRF of a biased agenda and misrepresenting India's multicultural society.
title: ‘Entity of concern’: Government lashes out at USCIRF

description: A major security breach in President Trump's administration revealed operational details of airstrikes against Yemeni Houthis via a leaked Signal chat. Top officials, including the defense secretary and national security adviser, were involved in the discussions. Despite the leak, the White House claims no classified information was compromised. This incident has raised concerns about the administration's handling of sensitive information.
title: 'Signal chat leak consequences for American pilots could have been catastrophic'

description: A hidden note of encouragement was found in the socks of Luigi Mangione, accused of murdering UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson. The court filing also revealed another message addressed to 'Joan,' while Mangione's supporters wore green in solidarity at the hearing. Mangione faces multiple charges both in state and federal courts.
title: 'Thousands wishing you luck': Secret note found in Luigi Mangione's socks

description: Elon Musk and the White House are investigating a Signal chat leak involving top national security officials and journalist Jeffrey Goldberg. Musk's technical experts aim to determine how Goldberg’s number was added to the group and to prevent similar incidents. Trump officials denied sharing classified information.
title: White House taps Elon Musk to investigate Signal app chat leak

description: A priest, Iyyagari Venkata Sai Krishna, was sentenced to life imprisonment for murdering aspiring TV actress, Kuruganti Apsara, in June 2023. He bludgeoned her to death and concealed her body in a sealed manhole. The court fined him Rs 10 lakh.
title: 'Dumped body in manhole': Priest gets life for killing aspiring actor
